    <div class="section-num">04 — Common Problems</div>
    <h2 class="section-title">Most Common American Range Failures in Los Angeles</h2>

    <div class="problems-grid">
      <div class="problem-card">
        <div class="problem-title">🔥 Open Burner Port Blockage</div>
        <div class="problem-cause">LA cooking oil combined with hard water deposits blocks individual star-cap ports — same pattern as BlueStar open burners. Yellow flame tips are the first sign. Wok and high-heat cooking produces more oil residue than standard cooking. We clear all star-cap ports on every American Range burner call — partial port restriction affects flame quality before it fails completely.</div>
        <span class="problem-tag tag-burner">Open Burner</span>
      </div>

      <div class="problem-card">
        <div class="problem-title">🌀 Uneven Innovection® Oven Results</div>
        <div class="problem-cause">Innovection® ring element partial degradation — the ring element surrounding the fan is losing output on one arc, creating a temperature imbalance in the convection airstream. Symptom looks like a fan problem. Test distinguishes: ring element resistance measurement shows the failing arc. We test the ring element specifically before any convection fan assessment on American Range oven calls.</div>
        <span class="problem-tag tag-convection">Innovection®</span>
      </div>

      <div class="problem-card">
        <div class="problem-title">🔆 Infrared Broil Not Working</div>
        <div class="problem-cause">Infrared element failure — typically abrupt (infrared elements tend to fail completely rather than degrade gradually). When infrared broil stops functioning while standard bake and convection modes work normally, the infrared element is the specific failure. The infrared element is a distinct component from the standard bake element — its replacement requires OEM American Range spec for the correct infrared output rating.</div>
        <span class="problem-tag tag-common">Wall Oven</span>
      </div>

      <div class="problem-card">
        <div class="problem-title">🔩 Igniter Failure — Coastal LA</div>
        <div class="problem-cause">Salt air corrosion on open burner igniters at coastal LA properties (Malibu, Pacific Palisades, Santa Monica, Manhattan Beach). American Range open burners have exposed igniter tips that face the same salt air acceleration as BlueStar and other open burner ranges. Coastal American Range installations benefit from annual igniter inspection — all tips checked, degraded igniters replaced proactively before intermittent ignition becomes no ignition.</div>
        <span class="problem-tag tag-coastal">Coastal LA</span>
      </div>

      <div class="problem-card">
        <div class="problem-title">🥘 Stock Pot Burner Output Loss</div>
        <div class="problem-cause">Gas valve restriction or large-orifice port blockage at the high-BTU stock pot burner position. The large gas orifice size at the stock pot burner accumulates a different blockage pattern than standard burner orifices — larger cooking oil particles and debris can affect the larger opening. Gas pressure at the stock pot position also merits assessment when output has dropped.</div>
        <span class="problem-tag tag-burner">Stock Pot</span>
      </div>

      <div class="problem-card">
        <div class="problem-title">🌡️ Oven Temperature Drift</div>
        <div class="problem-cause">Temperature sensor drift or thermostat calibration offset. American Range ovens use standard residential-spec thermostats and sensors available through the Chatsworth parts facility. We test with a calibrated probe before ordering — many temperature complaints resolve with calibration adjustment without parts. Post-calibration verification confirms the Innovection® system is producing even distribution at setpoint.</div>
        <span class="problem-tag tag-common">Most Common</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

