    <h2 class="section-title">American Range Repair FAQ</h2>

    <div class="faq-list">
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q">Where is American Range manufactured?</div>
        <div class="faq-a">Chatsworth, in the western San Fernando Valley — part of Los Angeles. American Range has been producing professional-grade cooking equipment in the Chatsworth facility since the 1970s, founded by the Demirjian family. It's one of the very few major professional range brands made in the United States, and the only one manufactured in Los Angeles.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q">What is Innovection® Convection and how is it different?</div>
        <div class="faq-a">Innovection® uses a ring-shaped heating element that surrounds the convection fan — delivering heat from 360 degrees around the fan. Standard convection typically has a single element behind or beside the fan. The ring element produces more even heat distribution and faster preheat. When Innovection® performance degrades, we test the ring element arc-by-arc — partial degradation produces intermediate symptoms that look like a fan problem until the element is measured specifically.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q">Why are my American Range burner flames yellow rather than blue?</div>
        <div class="faq-a">Open burner port blockage — the star-cap ports are partially blocked by cooking oil residue combined with LA hard water deposits. Yellow-tipped flames are the first sign of port restriction. In LA's cooking environment (especially at wok ring and high-heat positions), monthly inspection of star-cap ports is recommended for heavy cooking use. We clear all star-cap ports on every American Range burner call.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q">How quickly can you get American Range parts in LA?</div>
        <div class="faq-a">American Range is manufactured in Chatsworth — so for LA, parts lead times are dramatically shorter than European imports. Standard components (igniters, ring elements, thermostats, control boards) are typically available same-day or next-day. We call the Chatsworth facility (818-897-0808) before each job to confirm stock. This is a genuine local advantage that no European brand can match.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q">Do you service commercial American Range equipment in home kitchens?</div>
        <div class="faq-a">Yes. Some LA homeowners install commercial American Range units in their kitchens for maximum cooking performance. We service both residential pro-style and commercial American Range equipment. The service protocols are the same — open burner port service, Innovection® diagnosis for applicable models, Chatsworth parts. Commercial installation should include proper gas line sizing and professional hookup for optimal safety and performance.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q">How is the American Range open burner different from sealed burners on other ranges?</div>
        <div class="faq-a">Open burners (American Range, BlueStar, FiveStar) expose the burner cap and flame to the cooking surface — the flame is directly visible and accessible. Sealed burners (Bertazzoni, Fulgor Milano, GE) sit under a sealed cooktop surface with only the cap and grate visible. Open burners deliver higher BTU ceilings and a more intense, direct flame, but the exposed ports require regular maintenance. Sealed burners are easier to clean but have lower maximum output. The star-cap port cleaning protocol specific to open burners is the primary maintenance difference.</div>
